# AKOS Operations Delivery

Use this rule whenever authoring or executing **Operations area delivery** work —
PMO cadence, RevOps value-mapping execution, SMO service rhythm, Engagement client
delivery, executable catalog pairing, or I94 operational sweep tranches. Mechanical
companion to
[`OPERATIONS_DELIVERY_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Operations/OPERATIONS_DELIVERY_DISCIPLINE.md)
and
[`OPERATIONS_AREA_CHARTER.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Operations/OPERATIONS_AREA_CHARTER.md).

Upstream SSOT:
[`i94-operations-operational-sweep-thinking-synthesis-2026-06-10.md`](../../docs/wip/planning/94-area-architecture-and-completeness-v2/reports/i94-operations-operational-sweep-thinking-synthesis-2026-06-10.md).

## When this rule applies

- Mint or revise Operations root charter / delivery doctrine / README.
- Pair SOP+runbook for Operations `process_list.csv` rows (P2 tranche).
- Run or wire PMO automation (`render_wip_dashboard`, `render_operator_inbox`,
  `render_operational_cohesion_index`).
- Plan IntelligenceOps eviction or Engagement subfolder FK (P3 — operator gate).
- Score or improve Operations on `validate_area_completeness.py`.

## RULE 1 — DO vs REGISTER (binding)

Operations **executes** delivery loops; other areas **govern** domain doctrine.
Operations must not duplicate Data governance, Finance FINOPS policy, or People
methodology — only **trigger** handoffs (mirror emit, FINOPS bridge, compliance gates).

## RULE 2 — Automation-first pairing order (binding)

Per operator ratification Q2, pair runbooks in this order before broad AREA-09 cliff:

1. WIP / inbox / cohesion renders
2. Mirror emit trigger
3. Area completeness `--area Operations`
4. Engagement scaffold + RevOps dispatch
5. Remaining PMO/SMO SOPs

## RULE 3 — PMBOK domain map before new SOPs (binding)

New Operations SOPs must declare which PMBOK 7 performance domain they serve (see
OPERATIONS_DELIVERY_DOCTRINE §2). Project vs service is a **tag**, not a new sub-area.

## RULE 4 — Placement integrity (binding)

- **IntelligenceOps** is not Operations delivery — eviction to Research requires P3
  operator gate; no silent file moves.
- **business-strategy** under PMO is placement debt (I95 L6) — tracker only until
  inline-ratify.

## RULE 5 — Area-completeness worklist (binding)

Before Operations tranche commits:

```powershell
py scripts/validate_area_completeness.py --area Operations --next
py scripts/validate_area_completeness.py --area Operations --matrix
```

Work critical components to L3 first; closure gate = crit@L3 tier COMPLETE.

